1
00:03:13,931 --> 00:03:15,890
Elijah.

2
00:03:15,602 --> 00:03:16,729
Elijah.

3
00:03:17,661 --> 00:03:19,889
Elijah. Elijah.

4
00:03:20,907 --> 00:03:23,204
I am sorry, sir.
What is wrong with your arm?

5
00:03:23,284 --> 00:03:25,849
The cruel Romans..
- The Romans..

6
00:03:25,929 --> 00:03:28,280
For how long will our
God remain a mute witness?

7
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:31,129
Our God must have become old.

8
00:03:31,209 --> 00:03:34,490
Yes. Sometimes,
even I doubt the same.

9
00:03:34,129 --> 00:03:35,409
Doubt?

10
00:03:36,821 --> 00:03:38,900
Emmanuel.

11
00:03:39,337 --> 00:03:40,529
Elijah.

12
00:03:43,358 --> 00:03:44,569
Beware.

13
00:04:02,849 --> 00:04:04,209
Where will you escape?

14
00:04:04,289 --> 00:04:07,249
Let me go.
- I won't.

15
00:04:08,369 --> 00:04:10,900
Yes, I am an ape.

16
00:04:12,209 --> 00:04:15,900
Emmanuel, you are an ape.
- Sure, I am.

17
00:04:18,209 --> 00:04:20,409
Let me go. Let me go.

18
00:04:20,488 --> 00:04:23,600
Let me go.

19
00:04:33,209 --> 00:04:34,329
Yes, father.

20
00:04:35,289 --> 00:04:36,369
That is bad.

21
00:04:36,809 --> 00:04:40,329
You are a big boy now.
Big boys don't play on the streets.

22
00:04:40,489 --> 00:04:42,649
Even you never did?
- Never.

23
00:04:42,729 --> 00:04:46,890
When I was your age,
I never played on the streets.

24
00:04:46,289 --> 00:04:48,890
All right, father.
Then, even I shall not play.

25
00:04:48,169 --> 00:04:51,890
Bravo. My son is such a good boy.

26
00:04:51,169 --> 00:04:52,529
Right, Emmanuel?
- Yes, Master.

27
00:04:52,609 --> 00:04:54,769
Father, don't talk to Emmanuel.

28
00:04:54,849 --> 00:04:56,169
Why?

29
00:04:58,278 --> 00:05:01,161
I will not, son. Never.

30
00:05:01,361 --> 00:05:04,681
Look, I will be going to
meet an Egyptian merchant.

31
00:05:04,961 --> 00:05:07,410
I will be back soon, son.

32
00:05:23,121 --> 00:05:24,310
I won't drink that.

33
00:05:24,111 --> 00:05:28,521
Elijah. Oh God.
What kind of a bad omen is this.

34
00:05:30,961 --> 00:05:33,560
Everybody, beware.

35
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:38,921
The governor, the great Brutus,
is on his way.

36
00:06:13,761 --> 00:06:17,721
God knows better who is mad.

37
00:06:32,481 --> 00:06:35,201
Who threw the stone?
Where did it come from?

38
00:06:35,281 --> 00:06:38,481
From there. That boy over there.
- Arrest him. Get him.

39
00:06:40,761 --> 00:06:43,721
That boy threw the stone.
Arrest the little one of a snake.

40
00:07:00,401 --> 00:07:01,481
Emmanuel.

41
00:07:02,401 --> 00:07:04,761
Open the door or we
will break open it.

42
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:06,641
Open the door.
- Open the door.

43
00:07:06,721 --> 00:07:09,410
Open the door. - Open the
door or we will break open it.

44
00:07:09,121 --> 00:07:10,721
We will break open it.

45
00:07:11,281 --> 00:07:12,761
Open the door.

46
00:07:20,281 --> 00:07:21,361
Let go of him.

47
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,881
Emmanuel.
- Let go of him. Let go of my child.

48
00:07:24,201 --> 00:07:28,410
Let go of me. Emmanuel.
- Let go of my child. Look..

49
00:07:28,121 --> 00:07:30,800
Help.
- Where are you taking him?

50
00:07:30,161 --> 00:07:31,761
Where are you taking the child?

51
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:33,121
Move away.

52
00:07:33,201 --> 00:07:34,361
He is innocent.

53
00:07:34,561 --> 00:07:38,410
Emmanuel.

54
00:07:38,281 --> 00:07:41,201
Father. Father. Father.

55
00:07:41,281 --> 00:07:43,529
The criminal is here, My Lord.
- Let go of me.

56
00:07:47,921 --> 00:07:49,401
Elijah. Elijah.

57
00:07:49,481 --> 00:07:51,641
This child is not guilty.
He is not guilty.

58
00:07:51,721 --> 00:07:53,201
I know who is guilty.

59
00:07:53,281 --> 00:07:57,100
Mercy, My Lord. It was me who
had flung the stone. So punish me.

60
00:08:01,281 --> 00:08:06,810
Punishing one for the crime of
another is against Roman justice.

61
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:09,210
Take him away.
Throw him to the lions.

62
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:14,321
No, My Lord. Mercy, My Lord. Mercy.

63
00:08:14,841 --> 00:08:19,100
My Lord. Have mercy on my child.
- Emmanuel.

64
00:08:23,451 --> 00:08:25,801
Father.
- You can't take him. - Emmanuel.

65
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:36,241
Elijah. Elijah. Elijah.

66
00:08:37,616 --> 00:08:40,280
Elijah. Elijah.

67
00:08:54,241 --> 00:08:57,841
What is the matter, brothers?
What is it? Why are all of you so anxious?

68
00:09:00,281 --> 00:09:03,281
Emmanuel. Emmanuel,
why are you crying?

69
00:09:04,361 --> 00:09:07,561
Tell me. Tell me.
For God's sake, answer me.

70
00:09:08,201 --> 00:09:09,921
My Elijah is not harmed, is he?

71
00:09:13,561 --> 00:09:17,321
The cruel Brutus has ordered
Elijah to be thrown to the lions.

72
00:09:17,401 --> 00:09:18,560
Save him, Master.

73
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:21,810
No. No. This can never be.

74
00:09:21,721 --> 00:09:24,401
Elijah. Elijah.

75
00:09:29,180 --> 00:09:31,660
Father. Father.

76
00:09:31,820 --> 00:09:34,780
Come to me, my darling.

77
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:39,380
Father, where were you for so long?
I am very angry with you.

78
00:09:39,540 --> 00:09:42,540
Angry? Don't be, my dear.

79
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:46,180
You are the light of my eyes,
my peace of mind.

80
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:50,420
If you get angry with me,
then how am I going to live?

81
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:53,939
So, my darling is angry with me?
Go on, hit me.

82
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:57,859
Come on, hit me like this.
Like this. Like this.

83
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,740
Mercy!

84
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:03,540
Mercy! Mercy!

85
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:06,500
Have mercy.

86
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:08,420
Mercy, My Lord.

87
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:09,699
Move away, you wretch.

88
00:10:10,237 --> 00:10:14,380
Do not be afraid, dear. I have broken
his fangs. He cannot bite now.

89
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:16,820
Have mercy, My Lord. Have mercy.

90
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:20,580
Do not let the blood of a
lowly Jew taint your hands.

91
00:10:20,740 --> 00:10:22,740
Your virtues will be tarnished.

92
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:27,380
Unyielding as time, and firm as
steel, stands the law of Romans.

93
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,700
Go away.

94
00:10:30,940 --> 00:10:34,420
Forget not that there exists a
law taller than that of Romans.

95
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:36,580
That of God above.

96
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:39,500
Let not the hands of
nature's justice..

97
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,935
..reach out to your daughter
to avenge your heinous crime.

98
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:49,380
No. No. No. Have mercy,
My Lord. Have mercy.

99
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,940
May God protect your
daughter until eternity.

100
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:57,420
May God never make you
grieve for your child.

101
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:00,980
May the light of your
eyes never be extinguished.

102
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:11,699
My innocent one, have the
misdeed of a slave's son pardoned.

103
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:16,580
I implore at your tiny feet.

104
00:11:17,156 --> 00:11:20,939
With your dainty hands,
set free an innocent dove.

105
00:11:21,780 --> 00:11:24,180
And all his life, he
will pray for you.

106
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:34,780
Father, why is he crying? Pardon him.

107
00:11:35,380 --> 00:11:37,939
No, Lydia. He is a Jew.

108
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:41,579
So what? Pardon him.

109
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:47,780
No. Don't ever do that, my dear.

110
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:52,140
Go away, you shrewd Jew.
I forgive you.

111
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:55,380
Glory be to you.
Glory be to you, angel of mercy.

112
00:11:55,540 --> 00:11:58,420
Elijah. Elijah. You are free.

113
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:00,260
You are free.

114
00:12:04,940 --> 00:12:07,820
Elijah. Elijah.

115
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:11,540
Leave him. Leave my son.
He has been pardoned.

116
00:12:11,620 --> 00:12:12,660
Pardoned?

117
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:15,900
Yes. The merciful Brutus
has taken back his judgment.

118
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:19,140
But what is the proof?
- The proof?

119
00:12:19,386 --> 00:12:20,620
Ask him.

120
00:12:20,820 --> 00:12:24,180
Foolish Jew. Roman
justice is irrevocable.

121
00:12:24,574 --> 00:12:26,579
No. No.
- Father.

122
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:28,100
Elijah.
- Father.

123
00:12:28,180 --> 00:12:31,260
Elijah. Elijah.

124
00:12:54,503 --> 00:12:58,940
Master. It is all my fault.

125
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:05,260
My hands are tainted with
innocent Elijah's blood.

126
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:13,140
Kill me.

127
00:13:19,260 --> 00:13:24,100
Why don't you listen?
Master, why don't you listen?

128
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:27,500
Why don't you listen?

129
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:32,620
Revenge.

130
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:35,780
Revenge against the tyrant.

131
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:49,860
Father!

132
00:16:00,580 --> 00:16:04,620
Where is Lydia? Governess! Governess!

133
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:07,200
Where is Lydia?

134
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:09,100
She was sleeping right here, My Lord.

135
00:16:09,180 --> 00:16:11,300
Where? Her bed is empty.

136
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:14,339
Lydia!

137
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:19,260
Lydia! O'Douis! O'Douis!

138
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:24,180
O'Douis, find Lydia.
Hurry up. Go, find Lydia. Go!

139
00:16:39,620 --> 00:16:41,580
Why do you not speak?

140
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:43,380
Why do you not speak?

141
00:16:44,140 --> 00:16:45,260
Speak up.

142
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:46,780
My Lord, we searched every nook..

143
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:49,420
..and corner of the palace
but couldn't find her.

144
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,900
Silence. "Couldn't find her."

145
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:54,380
Couldn't find her, indeed.

146
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:58,460
Search for her, you scoundrels.
Search for her.

147
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:03,260
I know it in my heart.
This must be an evil Jew's work.

148
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:07,899
Search the home of every Jew.
Set their homes ablaze.

149
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:10,780
Do anything but get my Lydia back.

150
00:17:11,540 --> 00:17:14,253
Go. Immediately. Right now!

151
00:17:14,619 --> 00:17:19,699
Master. I have brought here
the apple of the enemy's eye.

152
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:26,540
Take this dagger and hack the
little one of Brutus into pieces.

153
00:17:30,294 --> 00:17:34,500
Oh. Grief has turned him to stone.

154
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:42,900
I presume I shall have to avenge
innocent Elijah's odious killing.

155
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:45,300
Father.
- Who is it?

156
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:48,220
Father.
- Who is it?

157
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:51,540
Father.
- Elijah. Elijah, my child.

158
00:17:51,740 --> 00:17:55,660
She is not Elijah but the object of
vengeance for Elijah's death, Master.

159
00:17:55,983 --> 00:17:58,600
The light of the tyrant Brutus' eyes.

160
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:03,139
Stab this dagger on her and
douse the raging fires of hatred.

161
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:06,860
No, Emmanuel. What wrong
has this innocent done?

162
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:10,200
Blood for blood,
Master. Here, take this.

163
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:12,200
No. No, Emmanuel. No.

164
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:16,340
You falter. If your hands tremble,
then I shall slay her.

165
00:18:16,420 --> 00:18:17,820
I shall slay her.

166
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:20,540
Emmanuel.
- Elijah, look. I shall seek vengeance.

167
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:23,939
Let go. Let go of her, you cruel man.

168
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,940
Look. Just look at that.

169
00:18:30,820 --> 00:18:34,600
Even she calls me
father just like Elijah did.

170
00:18:34,540 --> 00:18:39,860
Fear not, my dear. From this day,
you will take Elijah's place.

171
00:18:40,660 --> 00:18:44,140
Emmanuel, I have found my Elijah.

172
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:53,980
Open the door.

173
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:55,980
Open the door.

174
00:18:57,460 --> 00:18:58,660
Open the door.

175
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:01,180
Master, Roman soldiers.
You must take the child away.

176
00:19:01,260 --> 00:19:02,500
It is the decree of the
Emperor of Rome. Open the door.

177
00:19:03,288 --> 00:19:04,620
No. I cannot keep
her away from me now.

178
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:06,600
No. I cannot keep
her away from me now.

179
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:07,820
But..
- Open the door.

180
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:10,540
Open the door.

181
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:13,699
Master, there is nobody here.
Escape from the back door.

182
00:19:13,780 --> 00:19:16,460
It is the decree of the
Emperor of Rome. Open the door.

183
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:19,260
But, Emmanuel, you?
- I must stay back.

184
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:21,600
Or else they will follow you.
- But, Emmanuel..

185
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:24,220
Master. Go. For God's sake, go. Go.

186
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,500
Open the door.

187
00:19:28,719 --> 00:19:30,530
Open the door.

188
00:19:31,375 --> 00:19:34,950
It is the decree of The
Emperor of Rome. Open the door.

189
00:19:34,483 --> 00:19:35,883
Open the door.

190
00:19:37,763 --> 00:19:40,830
What is the noise for? Can you
not see it is so late at night?

191
00:19:40,164 --> 00:19:42,562
Silence. Where is Ezra, your master?

192
00:19:42,643 --> 00:19:44,443
He left the town this morning.

193
00:19:44,523 --> 00:19:47,122
We want to search this house.
Where is the girl?

194
00:19:47,203 --> 00:19:48,363
The girl?
- Yes.

195
00:19:48,443 --> 00:19:50,963
The one whom you kidnapped
from Governor Brutus' palace.

196
00:19:52,483 --> 00:19:54,883
This Roman man saw you.

197
00:20:00,569 --> 00:20:04,203
But this Roman didn't see..

198
00:20:04,443 --> 00:20:09,843
..how I hacked the tiny
child into small pieces..

199
00:20:13,683 --> 00:20:15,643
Go. Look for her there.

200
00:20:23,363 --> 00:20:29,283
Master, your slave..
has fulfilled his responsibility.

201
00:20:30,323 --> 00:20:31,923
Goodbye.

202
