226
00:24:06,403 --> 00:24:10,563
"Destined never to
smile and to weep forever."

227
00:24:10,643 --> 00:24:15,603
"This world, alas.
This world of ours."

228
00:24:15,683 --> 00:24:20,963
"The downtrodden are sneered at.
The helpless are oppressed."

229
00:24:31,283 --> 00:24:36,163
"This world."

230
00:24:49,763 --> 00:24:52,300
Salutations, Ezra.
- Salutations.

231
00:24:52,203 --> 00:24:54,322
Is this where you live these days?

232
00:24:54,403 --> 00:24:55,443
Yes.

233
00:24:55,916 --> 00:24:58,820
You have got a nice house.

234
00:24:58,323 --> 00:24:59,723
Yes, Abraham.

235
00:25:05,483 --> 00:25:07,723
How long it will
remain mine, only God knows.

236
00:25:07,803 --> 00:25:11,883
Don't say that "God knows".
Say, "the Romans knows".

237
00:25:12,243 --> 00:25:15,322
For quite some time now,
our God has left..

238
00:25:15,403 --> 00:25:20,123
..the lives and deaths of Jews
at the mercy of the cruel Romans.

239
00:25:20,483 --> 00:25:23,923
And He has made
Brutus the lord of hell.

240
00:25:47,203 --> 00:25:49,683
Hannah. Hannah.

241
00:26:23,683 --> 00:26:25,363
Thief.

242
00:26:25,563 --> 00:26:28,403
Am I a thief? Then I will throw
these out of the window, father.

243
00:26:28,483 --> 00:26:31,483
Don't do that. It is worth
ten thousand. Ten thousand.

244
00:26:31,563 --> 00:26:34,403
Shall I throw them out?
- Please don't, my dear.

245
00:26:34,483 --> 00:26:37,203
Ruth, stop her. She
may just throw them out.

246
00:26:37,283 --> 00:26:39,820
Don't you dare touch me.

247
00:26:41,243 --> 00:26:43,803
Here, keep your gems
worth ten thousand.

248
00:26:46,123 --> 00:26:48,163
Is my child angry?

