She? She is in. Why?
You have some work with her?

494
00:54:56,100 --> 00:54:57,940
I have work with you.

495
00:54:58,900 --> 00:55:00,420
With me?
- Yes.

496
00:55:01,182 --> 00:55:05,379
Tell me, what is it?
- Let me meet her.

497
00:55:09,620 --> 00:55:12,460
Working at a pretty girl's
house can be such a problem.

498
00:55:12,540 --> 00:55:13,620
Why?

499
00:55:13,700 --> 00:55:15,419
There is no value for me.

500
00:55:25,100 --> 00:55:26,140
This way.

501
00:55:43,140 --> 00:55:47,540
Chat with the cockatoo,
while I go and fetch madam.

502
00:55:48,180 --> 00:55:49,220
All right.

503
00:55:49,575 --> 00:55:50,785
Who?

504
00:55:54,380 --> 00:55:56,700
Did you ask me something?

505
00:55:59,380 --> 00:56:02,200
Don't stretch your neck too
much or it may get twisted.

506
00:56:02,180 --> 00:56:03,259
Shut up.

507
00:56:03,940 --> 00:56:08,660
Why get angry? I just said you
could end up twisting your neck.

508
00:56:08,740 --> 00:56:10,819
Shut up.
- Pali.

509
00:56:12,780 --> 00:56:16,460
Pali is very hot-tempered.
He got angry at me for no reason.

510
00:56:16,540 --> 00:56:18,340
Ruth has spoilt him rotten.

511
00:56:18,420 --> 00:56:20,288
Shut up. Shut up.

512
00:56:20,368 --> 00:56:22,140
Pali, he is a guest.

513
00:56:22,340 --> 00:56:24,460
Oh, my dear.

514
00:56:26,820 --> 00:56:28,740
Is he telling you or me?

515
00:56:29,220 --> 00:56:30,740
He just keeps on chattering.

516
00:56:32,620 --> 00:56:33,700
Can I be friends?

517
00:56:34,900 --> 00:56:36,940
Can I be friends?
- With whom?

518
00:56:38,100 --> 00:56:40,220
With your wise cockatoo.

519
00:56:40,940 --> 00:56:43,600
Are you very keen?
- Yes, I am.

520
00:56:43,544 --> 00:56:44,620
Then go ahead.

521
00:56:46,620 --> 00:56:47,700
Pali.

522
00:56:49,300 --> 00:56:51,540
I extend a hand of friendship to you.

523
00:56:53,260 --> 00:56:54,900
Pali. You fool.

524
00:56:59,980 --> 00:57:02,820
Never mind. I have no
right to impose myself.

525
00:57:03,380 --> 00:57:06,100
Oh, God. You are bleeding. Come here.

526
00:57:12,420 --> 00:57:13,740
You are bleeding so profusely.

527
00:57:16,780 --> 00:57:19,600
It is your hair that's
smelling so lovely, isn't it?

528
00:57:20,620 --> 00:57:23,779
I am terribly sorry.
Stupid Ruth has spoilt him.

529
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:26,380
But I think your
Pali is in love with me.

530
00:57:26,540 --> 00:57:29,460
Is this the way to express love?
- Then how does one express love?

531
00:57:29,644 --> 00:57:30,779
Pardon?

532
00:57:39,100 --> 00:57:42,540
It is bad manners to turn
your face away from a guest.

533
00:57:42,620 --> 00:57:44,380
No, I was only thinking.

534
00:57:44,780 --> 00:57:46,380
So was I.

535
00:57:46,820 --> 00:57:47,900
About what?

536
00:57:48,260 --> 00:57:51,820
How nice it would be if I were
to get what my heart seeks now.

537
00:57:53,980 --> 00:57:55,980
A doll as pretty as the moon.

538
00:57:59,220 --> 00:58:02,540
Then buy her.
- Money can't buy her.

539
00:58:02,740 --> 00:58:04,859
Why not?
- Because she seeks my heart.

540
00:58:05,900 --> 00:58:06,980
So give it to her.

541
00:58:07,780 --> 00:58:09,900
I already have.
- Then?

542
00:58:11,340 --> 00:58:13,380
I do not even know
if she has liked it.

543
00:58:14,340 --> 00:58:15,500
Then ask her.

544
00:58:20,620 --> 00:58:21,859
I am indeed asking.

545
00:58:26,500 --> 00:58:27,700
What's this?

546
00:58:37,220 --> 00:58:38,299
Why?

547
00:58:42,180 --> 00:58:45,500
There should be something
left even for tomorrow. Right?

548
00:58:45,580 --> 00:58:48,860
Yes. You must come tomorrow.
Father would be delighted.

549
00:58:50,780 --> 00:58:51,860
And what about you?

550
00:58:54,700 --> 00:58:57,200
Bid Pali adieu before you leave.
- Certainly not.

551
00:58:57,100 --> 00:59:00,259
Why?
- Teach him the ways of love first.

552
00:59:05,660 --> 00:59:06,740
Excuse me.

553
00:59:13,740 --> 00:59:14,819
Goodbye.

554
00:59:25,460 --> 00:59:28,180
Uncivilized bird. You don't
even know the ways of love.

555
00:59:29,380 --> 00:59:31,660
Madam, then you only teach him.

556
00:59:33,924 --> 00:59:35,860
Oh, my dear.

557
00:59:35,303 --> 00:59:38,263
"Oh, my dear."

558
00:59:38,463 --> 00:59:44,303
"I have fallen in love with someone."

559
00:59:44,463 --> 00:59:47,263
"What do I do?"

560
00:59:47,343 --> 00:59:49,942
"Oh, my dear."

561
00:59:50,143 --> 00:59:55,630
"I have fallen in love with someone."

562
00:59:55,143 --> 00:59:57,503
"What do I do?"

563
00:59:57,754 --> 01:00:02,703
"What do you do? What can anyone do?"

564
01:00:02,783 --> 01:00:07,823
"If you have lost your heart,
what can we do?"

565
01:00:07,903 --> 01:00:11,220
"Oh, my dear."

566
01:00:26,583 --> 01:00:31,503
"I was naive, I did not know."

567
01:00:47,423 --> 01:00:52,343
"I was naive, I did not know."

568
01:00:52,703 --> 01:00:57,503
"His look will make me lose my heart."

569
01:00:57,743 --> 01:01:02,903
"Neither would I have met him,
nor would I have lost my heart."

570
01:01:02,983 --> 01:01:07,983
"That's my mistake,
how can I complain?"

571
