592
01:03:09,503 --> 01:03:11,903
"Oh, my dear."

593
01:03:17,263 --> 01:03:19,823
"What do I do?"

594
01:03:19,903 --> 01:03:23,620
"Oh, my dear."

595
01:03:36,567 --> 01:03:39,543
My Lord, the Princess is here.
- Which princess?

596
01:03:39,623 --> 01:03:41,503
Indeed. There are two nowadays.

597
01:03:41,743 --> 01:03:43,230
One is yours, the other is Rome's.

598
01:03:43,103 --> 01:03:46,623
Which Princess, Leo?
- The Roman Princess, Octavia.

599
01:03:48,623 --> 01:03:50,623
At this hour?
- Yes, My Lord.

600
01:03:50,823 --> 01:03:53,220
You are a fool, Leo.
- Certainly not, Master.

601
01:03:53,423 --> 01:03:56,982
Tell her that I am not in the
palace or the gardens. Nowhere.

602
01:03:57,903 --> 01:03:58,903
Go.

603
01:04:00,459 --> 01:04:02,623
Then where are you?
- In hell.

604
01:04:08,966 --> 01:04:11,903
Where is Marcus, Leo?
- You mean my master?

605
01:04:12,183 --> 01:04:14,663
Yes.
- He has gone out.

606
01:04:14,903 --> 01:04:16,620
Where?
- To hell.

607
01:04:16,143 --> 01:04:19,103
What?
- I mean, I do not know.

608
01:04:19,397 --> 01:04:24,230
Why? Did you not tag behind
him today like a faithful dog?

609
01:04:24,143 --> 01:04:28,743
He said he wouldn't go hunting today,
so he wouldn't need a dog.

610
01:04:29,983 --> 01:04:34,423
Hadn't I asked you to remind
him about going out this evening?

611
01:04:34,503 --> 01:04:38,983
I did remind him, but he had
to leave on some secret mission.

612
01:04:46,490 --> 01:04:47,509
Please stop playing, Celia.

613
01:04:55,110 --> 01:04:57,150
Heartless man. Cruel one.

614
01:04:57,790 --> 01:04:58,830
Who, Princess?

615
01:04:59,550 --> 01:05:02,630
Who else but the one to
whom I have given my heart.

616
01:05:07,910 --> 01:05:08,990
Yasmine..

617
01:05:10,590 --> 01:05:11,910
Am I not beautiful?

618
01:05:13,390 --> 01:05:14,629
Does the mirror lie?

619
01:05:14,710 --> 01:05:16,150
Would the mirror dare lie, Princess?

620
01:05:16,230 --> 01:05:18,700
Then why does he not care for me?

621
01:05:18,590 --> 01:05:22,990
Why do my charms not work?
Why does he spurn me?

622
01:05:23,516 --> 01:05:26,830
But..- I had told him that
we would go out this evening.

623
01:05:27,786 --> 01:05:30,630
But he has gone
somewhere and left me desperate.

624
01:05:30,710 --> 01:05:33,430
Princess, he surely must have
been compelled to be secretive..

625
01:05:33,510 --> 01:05:35,510
Secretive? From me?

626
01:05:36,619 --> 01:05:39,510
Yasmine, there are no
secrets between two people in love.

627
01:05:52,270 --> 01:05:55,509
Look, Pali, listen
to me very carefully.

628
01:05:55,983 --> 01:05:58,230
You behaved very
badly with him yesterday.

629
01:05:58,311 --> 01:06:00,703
If he does not turn up today,
then I will not spare you.

630
01:06:02,634 --> 01:06:04,543
Shut up.
- You shut up.

631
01:06:04,861 --> 01:06:07,383
Who is it?
- "Who is it?" Nobody.

632
01:06:07,703 --> 01:06:09,679
What are you talking to Pali about?

633
01:06:09,759 --> 01:06:10,863
You?

634
01:06:11,743 --> 01:06:13,743
I have been waiting for someone.

635
01:06:14,543 --> 01:06:16,863
Oh, I see. Then I have
come at the wrong time.

636
01:06:20,103 --> 01:06:21,183
I will leave.

637
01:06:21,646 --> 01:06:23,743
Please don't.
- Why not?

638
01:06:28,110 --> 01:06:29,623
How is your hand?

639
01:06:31,379 --> 01:06:34,103
The wound has healed but
the scar still remains.

640
01:06:35,383 --> 01:06:37,942
The mark of love does not go
away that easily, does it?

641
01:06:39,623 --> 01:06:41,783
Why is the dressing
not removed? - Well..

642
01:06:48,641 --> 01:06:50,841
I hope it didn't hurt?
- What? My hand?

643
01:06:56,441 --> 01:06:58,361
So that's where it hurts?
- Yes.

644
01:06:59,601 --> 01:07:00,681
For how long will it remain?

645
01:07:17,441 --> 01:07:18,520
Are you happy?

646
01:07:19,721 --> 01:07:23,361
Why would I not be? I have
found something to live for.

647
01:07:31,601 --> 01:07:32,681
What's this?

648
01:07:33,441 --> 01:07:36,361
The necklace which you had lost
at the marketplace the other day.

649
01:07:36,801 --> 01:07:40,881
But this is not mine.
- Everything is yours.

650
01:07:42,281 --> 01:07:44,121
This dawn, its sunlight..

651
01:07:48,921 --> 01:07:50,681
..me, as well as everything I have.

652
01:07:53,121 --> 01:07:54,801
You want to ruin me.

653
01:07:55,401 --> 01:07:58,881
That's because you don't
want a thing. Tell me the truth.

654
01:08:00,121 --> 01:08:01,161
Me?

655
01:08:04,641 --> 01:08:07,681
I have got what I wanted.

656
01:08:12,401 --> 01:08:15,441
The necklace looks so lovely on you.

657
01:08:17,121 --> 01:08:19,241
Indeed. Like fetters
binding a prisoner.

658
01:08:20,161 --> 01:08:21,241
Tell me something.

659
01:08:22,281 --> 01:08:24,640
When will you be going home?
- Me?

660
01:08:27,481 --> 01:08:30,410
When death beckons me.
- Moshe.

661
01:08:33,528 --> 01:08:35,288
Did you ask for me, Princess?

662
01:08:37,648 --> 01:08:39,408
You look disturbed.

663
01:08:40,247 --> 01:08:43,407
Yes, Antonio, I am very disturbed.

664
01:08:45,368 --> 01:08:46,688
I fail to understand anything.

665
01:08:48,167 --> 01:08:52,928
Ever since the chariot mishap,
Marcus seems to be a changed man.

666
01:08:53,608 --> 01:08:56,480
The chariot mishap?
- Yes, Antonio.

667
01:08:56,848 --> 01:09:00,488
Can you find out for me, in
which world he remains lost?

668
01:09:00,808 --> 01:09:03,768
Do not worry,
Princess. I shall find out.

669
01:09:04,167 --> 01:09:06,647
I place complete faith in you, Antonio.
- Thank you.

670
01:09:13,928 --> 01:09:15,728
Yes, I remember.

671
01:09:56,168 --> 01:09:58,688
Why are you staring?

672
01:10:02,768 --> 01:10:04,968
Am I pretty?
- Undoubtedly.

673
01:10:10,328 --> 01:10:14,928
Wash off the muck some day and
look at yourself in the mirror.

674
01:10:15,168 --> 01:10:16,768
Even the mirror will
break with your shine.

675
01:10:17,768 --> 01:10:20,928
You look like a fairy.
A Persian fairy.

676
01:10:24,408 --> 01:10:28,208
No girl has wings. It is we
lover boys who give you wings.

677
01:10:29,968 --> 01:10:34,248
Augustine, look. There is
an admirer of mine here.

678
01:10:34,408 --> 01:10:37,128
Oh, no. Three would be a crowd.

679
01:10:37,208 --> 01:10:40,407
Love blossoms best in solitude.
In solitude.

680
01:10:50,811 --> 01:10:52,928
Get out of the way.

681
01:10:57,408 --> 01:10:59,880
You are getting angry.

682
01:10:59,168 --> 01:11:05,248
It is unbecoming for a man
like you to fight this way.

683
01:11:05,528 --> 01:11:07,488
Big brother. Big brother.

684
01:11:31,648 --> 01:11:34,368
Blind man. You broke my back.

685
01:11:34,448 --> 01:11:36,528
Broke your back?
Is it a back or a big sack?

686
01:11:54,968 --> 01:11:58,928
What would you like?
Apples, pomegranates, grapes?

687
01:12:02,408 --> 01:12:04,928
This seems to be a new shop? - No.

688
01:12:05,208 --> 01:12:07,728
But I give special
treatment for special customers.

689
01:12:09,968 --> 01:12:13,848
And who are you?
- Uncle, why not use a smaller fruit?

690
01:12:14,528 --> 01:12:16,568
He is my uncle. And he is a bit crazy.

691
01:12:16,648 --> 01:12:20,808
Crazy? My foot. Crazy? Am I crazy?

692
01:12:20,888 --> 01:12:24,248
Why should you be? But why do you
not realize that you are my uncle?

693
01:12:24,328 --> 01:12:26,448
Indeed. I am his father.

694
01:12:26,528 --> 01:12:29,408
What? You are my uncle.
- Oh, yes. His uncle.

695
01:12:29,728 --> 01:12:32,528
And these are real fresh.
Plucked from the orchards just now.

696
01:12:32,608 --> 01:12:35,800
Yes. - Take this.
- And this one is from me.

697
01:12:36,968 --> 01:12:40,800
How much is it? - How much?
To hell with the money.

698
01:12:41,768 --> 01:12:44,800
We don't need to. It grows on trees.

699
01:12:48,768 --> 01:12:50,208
Allow me to carry it till your house.

700
01:12:51,208 --> 01:12:52,728
In spite of being a Roman,
you are such a gentleman.

701
01:12:52,808 --> 01:12:54,568
Who told you so?
- What?

702
01:12:54,688 --> 01:12:56,528
Of course, I am a gentleman.

703
01:12:57,408 --> 01:12:59,528
Do you go to reach every
customer in this fashion?

704
01:13:00,608 --> 01:13:03,808
Well, that's a family trade. Let's go.

705
01:13:11,731 --> 01:13:13,858
You must be tired.
- Not at all.

706
01:13:14,369 --> 01:13:18,808
If need be, I could
even carry a customer.

707
01:13:19,101 --> 01:13:20,329
Really?
- Yes.

708
01:13:21,689 --> 01:13:23,633
Give it. This is my house.

709
01:13:24,969 --> 01:13:26,929
Is this your house?
- Yes.

710
01:13:31,607 --> 01:13:33,489
But why do you go to the market?

711
01:13:37,209 --> 01:13:39,129
And who do you think I am?
- Are you the maid?

712
01:13:39,649 --> 01:13:40,889
This..

713
01:13:40,969 --> 01:13:42,609
This house belongs to my Master,
Ezra, the jeweler.

714
01:13:42,689 --> 01:13:45,900
Oh, yes. I have heard
about Ezra, the jeweler..

715
01:13:48,169 --> 01:13:51,570
No. He has a daughter.
Her name is Hannah.

716
01:13:51,329 --> 01:13:52,648
The three of us live here.

717
01:13:52,729 --> 01:13:56,289
Three? Lies. There must be a
fourth person who visits here.

718
01:13:56,369 --> 01:13:57,969
Shut up. No one else comes here.

719
01:13:59,809 --> 01:14:01,625
Will you leave, or
should I call the others?

720
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:04,849
Sure. Provided they are pretty.

721
01:14:04,929 --> 01:14:06,809
Isaac.
- Louder.

722
01:14:06,889 --> 01:14:10,169
Jacob. - Isaac. Jacob.
These are names of men.

723
01:14:10,249 --> 01:14:13,169
Mozart. - Oh, my God.

724
01:14:13,449 --> 01:14:14,449
Jacob.

725
01:14:15,684 --> 01:14:16,819
Escaped.

726
01:14:40,572 --> 01:14:44,395
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

727
01:14:48,595 --> 01:14:51,555
"Oh, heart of me, hide
not from me and answer.."

728
