"From now on, should I call you
by a name your own or my beloved."

731
01:15:06,915 --> 01:15:10,875
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

732
01:15:24,475 --> 01:15:28,595
"To you I listen and
will continue to."

733
01:15:28,675 --> 01:15:32,556
"The torment I feel I will conceal."

734
01:15:37,395 --> 01:15:41,480
"How much more
should I control myself?"

735
01:15:41,421 --> 01:15:43,750
"Walking hither and thither.."

736
01:15:46,235 --> 01:15:49,594
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

737
01:15:49,675 --> 01:15:52,595
"Oh, heart of me, hide
not from me and answer.."

738
01:15:52,675 --> 01:15:57,350
"From now on, should I call you
by a name your own or my beloved."

739
01:15:57,115 --> 01:16:00,795
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

740
01:16:18,875 --> 01:16:23,115
"Oh, eyes so intoxicating,
what have you done?"

741
01:16:23,195 --> 01:16:26,995
"For what do you seek vengeance?"

742
01:16:27,520 --> 01:16:31,755
"An effect so
devastating these eyes had on me.."

743
01:16:31,835 --> 01:16:35,897
"That my heart was beyond my control."

744
01:16:35,977 --> 01:16:37,595
"Walking hither and thither.."

745
01:16:40,675 --> 01:16:43,995
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

746
01:16:47,148 --> 01:16:51,475
"From now on, should I call you
by a name your own or my beloved."

747
01:16:51,555 --> 01:16:55,355
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

748
01:17:08,794 --> 01:17:12,755
"My thoughts are all about you.
I grieve too only for you."

749
01:17:17,275 --> 01:17:21,195
"To even my slumber I say.."

750
01:17:21,595 --> 01:17:25,755
"Let him be present
even in my dreams."

751
01:17:25,835 --> 01:17:27,155
"Walking hither and thither.."

752
01:17:30,235 --> 01:17:33,554
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

753
01:17:33,675 --> 01:17:36,555
"Oh, heart of me, hide
not from me and answer.."

754
01:17:36,635 --> 01:17:40,915
"From now on, should I call you
by a name your own or my beloved."

755
01:17:40,995 --> 01:17:44,394
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

756
01:17:44,475 --> 01:17:47,235
"Oh, heart of me, hide
not from me and answer.."

757
01:17:47,315 --> 01:17:51,674
"From now on, should I call you
by a name your own or my beloved."

758
01:17:51,755 --> 01:17:55,115
"Walking hither and
thither came along someone."

759
01:18:38,420 --> 01:18:40,453
Welcome, Emperor. Welcome.

760
01:18:41,330 --> 01:18:44,293
By the grace of God,
may you live long.

761
01:18:59,853 --> 01:19:03,733
I do not know either.
Perhaps he has gone hunting

762
01:19:06,137 --> 01:19:08,333
He remains unfettered
by responsibilities.

763
01:19:09,253 --> 01:19:12,973
The zeal of youth is
like a gust of strong wind.

764
01:19:15,979 --> 01:19:18,573
I too have lived
through such years, Octavia.

765
01:19:19,173 --> 01:19:22,933
But, my dear, your marriage
must not be delayed any further.

766
01:19:28,263 --> 01:19:30,492
There is a difference between
coyness and refusal, Octavia.

767
01:19:31,176 --> 01:19:33,150
Are you not happy with this match?

768
01:19:33,223 --> 01:19:36,175
I am happy, My Lord. I am very happy.

769
01:19:57,975 --> 01:20:01,550
Take a look at this diamond,
Moshe. It is so extraordinary.

770
01:20:01,695 --> 01:20:03,695
It is indeed very extraordinary.

771
01:20:04,455 --> 01:20:06,295
Truly exquisite and flawless.

772
01:20:09,980 --> 01:20:13,815
But, father, one needs to be very
lucky to get something as exquisite.

773
01:20:16,845 --> 01:20:18,405
With hard work and sacrifice.

774
01:20:21,160 --> 01:20:25,485
How do you like her reply?
None can defeat my daughter.

775
01:20:29,325 --> 01:20:31,450
Who could it be at this hour?

776
01:20:32,245 --> 01:20:34,925
Ruth. - Yes?

777
01:20:35,645 --> 01:20:37,245
Go and see who is at the door.

778
01:20:47,125 --> 01:20:48,885
Is this the jeweler Ezra's house?

779
01:20:56,405 --> 01:20:57,445
Please come.

780
01:20:59,238 --> 01:21:00,845
Princess Octavia.

781
01:21:00,925 --> 01:21:02,685
Blessed am I.

782
01:21:03,165 --> 01:21:08,485
Thank you for coming here.
What can this slave do for you?

783
01:21:08,765 --> 01:21:10,445
Are you Ezra, the jeweler?

784
01:21:10,605 --> 01:21:12,844
Yes, Princess. Please be seated.

785
01:21:19,161 --> 01:21:20,780
Moshe. What are you doing?

786
01:21:20,860 --> 01:21:23,205
Look at that apple there.
- Forget the apple.

787
01:21:23,285 --> 01:21:24,925
I must get it.
- Forget it.

788
01:21:25,646 --> 01:21:29,525
The axle of my chariot is broken.
Please have it repaired.

789
01:21:30,364 --> 01:21:32,804
I must return early. Or
the Emperor will be anxious.

790
01:21:32,965 --> 01:21:34,525
Do not worry, Princess.

791
01:21:34,805 --> 01:21:38,805
Till the chariot gets repaired,
please rest here.

792
01:21:39,162 --> 01:21:42,485
Hannah, go and get
some fruits and sherbet.

793
01:21:42,845 --> 01:21:43,885
Very well, father.

794
01:21:48,765 --> 01:21:52,405
If you wish, you may
look at these jewels.

795
01:21:53,245 --> 01:21:57,288
Where are you going, Moshe?
- To.. to fix the chariot.

796
01:21:57,368 --> 01:22:02,125
No, no. You must stay here.
Look after the royal guests.

797
01:22:02,205 --> 01:22:05,285
Such a guest could
craft a man's destiny.

798
01:22:05,365 --> 01:22:06,925
I will attend to the chariot.

799
01:22:07,483 --> 01:22:08,890
Don't take..

800
01:22:16,245 --> 01:22:18,565
Yasmine, this is lovely.

801
01:22:18,885 --> 01:22:21,565
Princess, just take
a look at that man.

802
01:22:21,805 --> 01:22:24,205
He bears a striking
resemblance with Prince Marcus.

803
01:22:24,525 --> 01:22:25,565
Ask him his name.

804
01:22:27,953 --> 01:22:31,445
Excuse me.
- Yes? - Who are you?

805
01:22:32,645 --> 01:22:38,165
A creation of God who
crafted this wonderful world.

806
01:22:41,135 --> 01:22:43,565
But why are you hiding your face?

807
01:22:44,459 --> 01:22:45,965
The cruel woman will beat me.

808
01:22:47,885 --> 01:22:49,205
Who will beat you?

809
01:22:49,525 --> 01:22:54,850
The one who is
preparing sherbet for you.

810
01:22:55,285 --> 01:22:56,845
But why would she beat you?

811
01:22:57,605 --> 01:23:00,764
In a moment of weakness in love..

812
01:23:00,845 --> 01:23:04,325
..I promised her never to
show my face to another woman.

813
01:23:09,765 --> 01:23:11,365
But we can be quite adamant.

814
01:23:17,365 --> 01:23:20,500
Are you a man or a rabbit?

815
01:23:22,965 --> 01:23:25,885
A rabbit I am not.

816
01:23:40,805 --> 01:23:41,965
Who is he?

817
01:23:42,725 --> 01:23:43,765
Him?

818
01:23:44,565 --> 01:23:47,525
He has a gift of the gab. But
why doesn't he show his face?

819
01:23:48,445 --> 01:23:49,485
He is shy.

820
01:23:50,365 --> 01:23:53,365
Shy? Or is he sold out?

821
01:23:55,885 --> 01:23:58,605
Princess, your chariot is ready.

822
01:23:59,245 --> 01:24:01,245
Thank you very much
for your hospitality.

823
01:24:02,805 --> 01:24:07,165
I have selected some jewelry.
Please have it sent over.

824
01:24:07,245 --> 01:24:09,605
With pleasure. Blessed are my stars.

825
01:24:24,205 --> 01:24:26,365
Yes. But why were
you hiding from them?

826
01:24:26,445 --> 01:24:29,245
Me? Of course not. When did I hide?

827
01:24:29,325 --> 01:24:31,764
I was only..

828
01:24:32,845 --> 01:24:33,885
Listen..

829
01:24:34,388 --> 01:24:36,245
That woman..
- The Princess?

830
01:24:36,445 --> 01:24:41,724
No. Her slave. She was staring at me.

831
01:24:48,365 --> 01:24:50,844
I will leave now.

832
01:24:55,245 --> 01:24:58,125
Strange are Your ways, God.

833
01:24:58,205 --> 01:25:00,165
Strange are the ways
which destiny leads one to.

834
01:25:00,449 --> 01:25:03,804
The Princess of Rome comes
to the door of a petty Jew.

835
01:25:04,165 --> 01:25:08,245
Moshe. - Excuse me. Permit
to leave. - So soon? No way.

836
01:25:08,325 --> 01:25:10,165
You cannot leave until night, today.

837
01:25:10,365 --> 01:25:11,925
Why? Anything special?

838
01:25:14,205 --> 01:25:15,845
It is an auspicious day today.

839
01:25:18,285 --> 01:25:22,325
Oh, yes. I will be
surely coming tonight.

840
01:25:22,405 --> 01:25:24,565
Do come. Do come.

841
01:25:32,685 --> 01:25:34,165
I am at your service, My Lord.

842
01:25:35,485 --> 01:25:37,325
I was eager to see you, Marcus.

843
01:25:42,285 --> 01:25:43,485
Very well, My Lord.

844
01:25:43,605 --> 01:25:49,840
I wish to bind your wayward feet
with fetters of responsibility.

845
01:25:49,565 --> 01:25:52,844
With the passing of
this phase of the moon..

846
01:25:52,925 --> 01:25:55,125
..I want you to get married.

847
01:25:55,725 --> 01:25:58,850
Do you comply with my wishes?

848
01:26:00,925 --> 01:26:01,965
Why are you silent?

849
01:26:06,200 --> 01:26:09,804
Marcus. I shall
overlook your audaciousness.

850
01:26:09,965 --> 01:26:12,165
Go. You are given time to think.

851
01:26:12,285 --> 01:26:15,943
I would also seek the freedom
to decide for myself, My Lord.

852
01:26:53,805 --> 01:26:54,845
Son..

853
01:27:00,725 --> 01:27:05,450
My fellow-brothers, eating
this holy bread implies..

854
01:27:05,445 --> 01:27:08,217
..affirming our
allegiance to the true God..

855
01:27:08,297 --> 01:27:10,285
..and to the doctrine of
the religion of the Jews.

856
01:27:10,685 --> 01:27:13,845
The one who eats this
bread is a true Jew.

857
01:27:13,965 --> 01:27:15,685
No doubt.

858
01:27:26,445 --> 01:27:27,724
Where are you going, Moshe?

859
01:27:59,133 --> 01:28:00,285
Moshe.

860
01:28:12,285 --> 01:28:15,805
You lied to father. Why did
you throw away the holy bread?

861
01:28:17,485 --> 01:28:18,525
Who said so?

862
01:28:19,805 --> 01:28:20,845
What's this?

863
01:28:22,125 --> 01:28:24,365
I saw you drop the
bread with my own eyes.

864
01:28:25,405 --> 01:28:27,850
No Jew would ever do that.

865
01:28:38,925 --> 01:28:39,970
Hannah.

866
01:28:40,845 --> 01:28:45,125
Do not touch me. I did not know
that you could lie even to me.

867
01:28:45,725 --> 01:28:48,605
Do not cast suspicions
inside a heart filled with love.

868
01:28:54,525 --> 01:28:57,405
Then why do you not
clearly say what the matter is?

869
01:28:58,765 --> 01:29:02,325
I am unable to
express what's on my mind.

870
01:29:03,290 --> 01:29:07,850
I will tell my Hannah everything.
Everything.

871
01:29:07,165 --> 01:29:08,245
Hannah.

872
01:29:09,965 --> 01:29:12,205
You have guests at home.
So go inside now, Hannah.

873
01:29:13,165 --> 01:29:16,405
I shall wait for you
tonight near the ruins.

874
01:29:16,619 --> 01:29:18,850
No. I cannot come there.

875
01:29:18,485 --> 01:29:20,644
Do not be adamant, Hannah.
You have to come.

876
01:29:21,365 --> 01:29:24,165
No. Say what you must, here and now.

877
01:29:24,325 --> 01:29:26,245
Dear, the guests are leaving.

878
01:29:28,285 --> 01:29:30,445
If in my heart, lies love for you..

879
01:29:31,165 --> 01:29:35,245
..and if my love for you is true,
then you will come there.

880
01:29:36,644 --> 01:29:37,685
You surely will.

881
01:30:14,439 --> 01:30:23,679
"Madly in love with you I am."

882
01:30:25,879 --> 01:30:31,959
"Of my love, very proud I am."

883
01:30:33,359 --> 01:30:37,999
"You may believe it or not."

884
01:30:39,239 --> 01:30:45,159
"But people sure will."

885
01:30:45,999 --> 01:30:50,639
"Call it a streak of insanity."

886
01:30:50,959 --> 01:30:55,239
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

887
01:30:55,639 --> 01:31:00,390
"Call it a streak of insanity."

888
01:31:00,359 --> 01:31:04,519
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

889
01:31:09,839 --> 01:31:14,239
"Then only you are to be blamed."

890
01:31:14,359 --> 01:31:18,679
"Call it a streak of insanity."

891
01:31:37,599 --> 01:31:42,790
"The heart yearns only for you."

892
01:31:42,319 --> 01:31:46,479
"In love I am, only with you."

893
01:31:46,799 --> 01:31:51,439
"The heart yearns only for you."

894
01:31:51,559 --> 01:31:55,719
"In love I am, only with you."

895
01:31:56,199 --> 01:32:00,398
"You may or may not come here."

896
01:32:00,759 --> 01:32:05,119
"But wait I will for you."

897
01:32:05,519 --> 01:32:09,759
"Call it a streak of insanity."

898
01:32:10,239 --> 01:32:14,358
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

899
01:32:14,748 --> 01:32:23,678
"If this you fail to fathom
then only you are to be blamed."

900
01:32:23,759 --> 01:32:28,119
"Call it a streak of insanity."

901
01:32:46,799 --> 01:32:51,319
"In such solitude and wilderness.."

902
01:32:51,476 --> 01:32:55,558
"Stifled to death I will be."

903
01:33:00,719 --> 01:33:04,839
"Stifled to death I will be."

904
01:33:05,199 --> 01:33:09,518
"Beckon me a million times then."

905
01:33:10,119 --> 01:33:14,119
"But return I will never."

906
01:33:14,479 --> 01:33:18,719
"Call it a streak of insanity."

907
01:33:23,679 --> 01:33:27,879
"If this you fail to fathom.."

908
01:33:28,190 --> 01:33:32,558
"Then only you are to be blamed."

909
01:33:32,799 --> 01:33:36,919
"Call it a streak of insanity."

910
01:33:37,439 --> 01:33:41,999
"Call it a streak of insanity."

911
01:33:43,442 --> 01:33:44,479
Moshe.

912
01:33:52,759 --> 01:33:54,359
I was sure you would come.

913
01:33:56,439 --> 01:33:57,759
Come close to me, Hannah.

914
01:33:58,876 --> 01:34:01,359
Look, how my heart
implores before you.

915
01:34:02,639 --> 01:34:05,319
For peace. For love.

916
01:34:05,772 --> 01:34:07,559
Convince me, Moshe.

917
01:34:07,999 --> 01:34:14,790
Compel me to
understand whatever you say.

918
01:34:19,999 --> 01:34:21,390
Look here, Hannah.

919
01:34:23,217 --> 01:34:25,790
Look into my eyes.

920
01:34:26,758 --> 01:34:28,879
Moshe, your body
burns with high fever.

921
01:34:29,119 --> 01:34:32,679
My soul burns in the fires
of love, Hannah. Douse it.

922
01:34:33,959 --> 01:34:36,159
What.. what am I to do?

923
01:34:36,943 --> 01:34:41,639
Have faith in me.
Doubt not my love, Hannah.

924
01:34:43,679 --> 01:34:48,359
Moshe, words are not
enough to quell away doubts.

925
01:34:49,508 --> 01:34:52,239
Tell me the truth. Are you not a Jew?

926
01:34:55,796 --> 01:34:57,160
Why are you silent?

927
01:35:01,999 --> 01:35:05,611
One word from me, and a
storm of sorrows may break free.

928
01:35:06,719 --> 01:35:09,879
Our love may get poisoned
with hatred.

929
01:35:11,759 --> 01:35:14,319
Hannah, is it possible
that I could lose you forever?

930
01:35:14,760 --> 01:35:18,239
Moshe. Tell me that
you are not a Roman.

931
01:35:18,436 --> 01:35:22,759
I am human. Captivated by
your love, and helpless.

932
01:35:23,199 --> 01:35:26,799
Moshe, tell me that you
are not a Roman. Say it.

933
01:35:27,519 --> 01:35:28,559
Hannah.

934
01:35:32,159 --> 01:35:37,279
If humans are known by such names..

935
01:35:38,839 --> 01:35:40,446
..then yes, I am a Roman.

936
01:35:48,279 --> 01:35:50,359
But there's no
injustice greater than this.

937
01:35:52,759 --> 01:35:54,639
No punishment harsher than this.

938
01:35:54,719 --> 01:35:59,799
Don't touch me. You have cheated me.
What harm had I done to you? tell me.

939
01:35:59,919 --> 01:36:01,318
You have given me life.

940
01:36:02,646 --> 01:36:06,920
With your love, you have
brought light into my dark life.

941
01:36:06,172 --> 01:36:07,358
Lies.

942
01:36:07,719 --> 01:36:12,429
Oh, cruel man, wipe off the
false twinkle of love from your eyes.

943
01:36:12,883 --> 01:36:15,174
Do not look at me that way.
Go away, Moshe.

944
01:36:16,774 --> 01:36:20,540
Hannah.
- I wish to hear no more.

945
01:36:20,454 --> 01:36:22,334
Only because I am a Roman?

946
01:36:23,494 --> 01:36:26,534
Hannah, look not at my religion.
Look at my heart, my love.

947
01:36:27,214 --> 01:36:31,494
I have seen steel, and I've
seen stone. Go away, Moshe. Go.

948
01:36:36,594 --> 01:36:41,374
Hannah, my love, your love has
pervaded every fiber of my being.

949
01:36:47,574 --> 01:36:50,773
In these lonely valleys,
I shall die a slow, agonizing death.

950
01:36:52,694 --> 01:36:56,940
Till my last breath, only your
name will be present on my lips.

951
01:36:57,494 --> 01:37:01,348
But this much, I do promise.
You will never hear my voice again.

952
01:37:01,429 --> 01:37:04,750
Enough. Enough, Moshe. Enough.

953
01:37:07,498 --> 01:37:08,933
Take me away somewhere.

954
01:37:09,552 --> 01:37:13,614
I can live with the
dishonor and seclusion.

955
01:37:13,958 --> 01:37:19,214
But I cannot bear to be away
from you and lead a stifled life.

956
01:37:20,444 --> 01:37:25,534
Then, let us go to a place
where men do not fight over Gods.

957
01:37:26,607 --> 01:37:30,894
Where even the shadow of this
traitorous world won't be cast.

958
01:37:32,350 --> 01:37:33,534
Come, Hannah.

959
01:37:33,694 --> 01:37:37,374
Wait. Where are you running?

960
01:37:39,374 --> 01:37:42,534
This escape will be very difficult.

961
01:37:42,814 --> 01:37:46,214
You will be ruined by my curse
that will come from deep within.

962
01:37:46,294 --> 01:37:47,414
Father.

963
01:37:48,614 --> 01:37:50,414
Ungrateful Roman.

964
01:37:50,938 --> 01:37:53,614
Is this why you
entered my house as a guest?

965
01:37:54,134 --> 01:37:57,774
To lead my daughter into sin?

966
01:37:57,854 --> 01:37:59,894
I will not spare you alive today.

967
01:37:59,974 --> 01:38:02,334
Father. He is innocent.
- Step aside, Hannah.

968
01:38:06,614 --> 01:38:10,693
Coward Roman. Have your
arms no strength anymore?

969
01:38:14,619 --> 01:38:18,120
Do you have a heart, a
soul of a human being..

970
01:38:20,134 --> 01:38:24,349
Sly Roman. I am well aware
of your wicked Roman ways.

971
01:38:24,429 --> 01:38:28,694
You know nothing. Your eyes are
shrouded with misconceptions. - Moshe.

972
01:38:29,374 --> 01:38:32,755
In the name of religion, you
want to strangle true love. - Moshe.

973
01:38:32,835 --> 01:38:35,654
I want to rip the
weed off by its roots.

974
01:38:36,147 --> 01:38:38,734
I shall hang your body
at the crossroads of Rome.

975
01:38:39,254 --> 01:38:42,934
As a lesson to be learnt for
treacherous Romans like you.

976
01:38:46,854 --> 01:38:49,614
I am in love with him. I am
the one who's caused you pain.

977
01:38:49,694 --> 01:38:53,334
Silence, you naive girl. You
do not know what you are saying.

978
01:38:53,454 --> 01:38:54,813
The truth, father.

979
01:38:55,374 --> 01:38:59,809
Give me my dreams, my love,
my desire as alms, father.

980
01:38:59,890 --> 01:39:03,374
Never. Get out of my way.
Or even you will be..

981
01:39:03,494 --> 01:39:05,174
With pleasure, father.
Kill me. Kill me.

982
01:39:05,254 --> 01:39:08,733
I will give up my life at your feet.

983
01:39:14,134 --> 01:39:15,374
Alas.

984
