02:04:16,532 --> 02:04:19,972
..that in the eyes of law,
the weak and mighty are equal.

1214
02:04:20,612 --> 02:04:26,612
Let him not enjoy any privileges
just because he is Crown Prince.

1215
02:04:40,412 --> 02:04:43,612
'How nice it would be if I were
to get what my heart seeks now.'

1216
02:04:43,692 --> 02:04:45,132
'And what does the heart seek?'

1217
02:04:45,532 --> 02:04:48,132
'A doll as pretty as the moon.'

1218
02:05:15,812 --> 02:05:17,120
Oh, my dear.

1219
02:05:44,892 --> 02:05:47,572
'Your love has pervaded
every fiber of my being.'

1220
02:05:48,492 --> 02:05:51,172
'At your feet, I shall end my life.'

1221
02:05:51,854 --> 02:05:55,772
'Till my last breath, only your
name will be present on my lips.'

1222
02:06:11,692 --> 02:06:12,772
Hannah.

1223
02:06:14,815 --> 02:06:17,371
Princess. You?

1224
02:06:17,612 --> 02:06:18,892
Yes.

1225
02:06:20,296 --> 02:06:22,252
I am here to implore for mercy.

1226
02:06:24,172 --> 02:06:26,692
Why must you mock at my helplessness?

1227
02:06:27,497 --> 02:06:31,772
What can a poor Jewess
give to the Princess of Rome?

1228
02:06:32,332 --> 02:06:34,732
Everything is in your
hands today, Hannah.

1229
02:06:35,372 --> 02:06:39,772
Marcus' future lies
at your discretion.

1230
02:06:41,252 --> 02:06:46,852
To make your love a success,
you seek the aid of a helpless girl?

1231
02:06:47,452 --> 02:06:49,772
Do not consider me your enemy, Hannah.

1232
02:06:50,932 --> 02:06:55,452
Even I am a woman.
I can understand the pain you feel.

1233
02:06:55,932 --> 02:06:59,972
But why have you shelved your
honor and come to console me?

1234
02:07:11,492 --> 02:07:17,812
The difference being, you are
triumphant, and I have failed.

1235
02:07:18,972 --> 02:07:21,932
Sweet words do not
soothe the heart, Princess.

1236
02:07:22,492 --> 02:07:24,932
If you had a woman's heart, then..

1237
02:07:29,572 --> 02:07:34,452
You have made a mockery of love
and robbed me of my love. Leave.

1238
02:07:34,532 --> 02:07:38,572
Hannah. - For God's sake,
go away. And leave me alone.

1239
02:07:39,452 --> 02:07:42,892
I will leave. But hear me out.

1240
02:07:43,919 --> 02:07:46,932
Because of you, the man you
love will be sentenced to death.

1241
02:07:49,680 --> 02:07:50,972
Sentenced to death?

1242
02:07:55,412 --> 02:07:57,692
I occupy the seat of justice now.

1243
02:08:03,452 --> 02:08:09,652
..will affect not only you,
but the Roman Empire and its future.

1244
02:08:10,652 --> 02:08:14,332
In this court of justice,
I give you one more opportunity.

1245
02:08:15,172 --> 02:08:17,172
I ask you once more.

1246
02:08:17,852 --> 02:08:21,120
Are the charges made by the
Jew and his daughter true or not?

1247
02:08:26,532 --> 02:08:28,612
I don't wish to
waste the court's time..

1248
02:08:28,692 --> 02:08:30,819
..by repeating my statements.

1249
02:08:31,132 --> 02:08:34,411
The allegations levied by the
Jew and his daughter are true.

1250
02:08:34,852 --> 02:08:37,932
No, My Lord. I wish to say something.

1251
02:08:43,372 --> 02:08:46,332
My Lord, the prince is innocent.

1252
02:08:46,412 --> 02:08:50,771
Hannah. - I take back the
charges cast on the Prince.

1253
02:08:51,212 --> 02:08:54,132
I made a mistake in
identifying the accused.

1254
02:08:55,492 --> 02:09:01,212
The same face, the same clothes.
Everything seemed identical.

1255
02:09:02,132 --> 02:09:05,520
But he.. he was not the one.

1256
02:09:05,732 --> 02:09:08,292
The Prince has not disgraced me.

1257
02:09:08,812 --> 02:09:10,852
My Lord, she is lying.

1258
02:09:11,252 --> 02:09:14,972
She wishes to burden
Rome's throne with her kindness.

1259
02:09:17,532 --> 02:09:23,492
So, the actual criminal
resembled Prince Marcus?

1260
02:09:25,252 --> 02:09:26,286
Yes, My Lord.

1261
02:09:26,557 --> 02:09:29,920
Is that why you crossed your limits..

1262
02:09:29,612 --> 02:09:32,532
..and accused the
Crown Prince of Rome?

1263
02:09:33,412 --> 02:09:34,732
Yes, My Lord.

1264
02:09:36,772 --> 02:09:40,332
And the Jew who screamed at
the top of his voice yesterday.

1265
02:09:40,692 --> 02:09:42,920
Why are you silent today?

1266
02:09:42,286 --> 02:09:46,612
Do not provoke me any further.
Put an end to this story.

1267
02:09:46,932 --> 02:09:51,520
If I speak the truth, your heart
will burn. And that's my word.

1268
02:09:51,332 --> 02:09:57,372
I swear by my helplessness that
the flames raging in my heart..

1269
02:09:57,492 --> 02:10:01,132
..are enough to burn
all of Rome to ashes.

1270
02:10:01,772 --> 02:10:05,892
But no. I cannot break her heart.

1271
02:10:06,852 --> 02:10:09,892
Today, the one I love has
compelled me to remain silent.

1272
02:10:10,892 --> 02:10:13,331
I accept the verdict
which I am destined for.

1273
02:10:13,532 --> 02:10:16,852
So much so, that I am ready to
obey your untrue verdict too.

1274
02:10:16,932 --> 02:10:21,172
If my verdict is not heeded,
the person will not be spared, Ezra.

1275
02:10:22,372 --> 02:10:26,532
Prince Marcus is declared not guilty.

1276
02:10:28,292 --> 02:10:34,452
Hannah, you wrongly testified
against Rome's Crown Prince.

1277
02:10:39,572 --> 02:10:44,120
And your father, Ezra,
was an accomplice to your crime.

1278
02:10:45,132 --> 02:10:51,652
For maligning the royal family,
you are declared its enemies.

1279
02:10:52,332 --> 02:10:56,332
And sentenced to death in
containers of boiling oil.

1280
02:10:57,532 --> 02:10:58,852
My Lord!

1281
02:11:03,670 --> 02:11:07,190
What have you done, My Lord?
She is innocent.

1282
02:11:07,735 --> 02:11:11,700
She misled the court
because of her blind love for me.

1283
02:11:11,270 --> 02:11:15,270
It is evidence that
matters in court, not emotions.

1284
02:11:15,350 --> 02:11:18,270
But it is no justice to
sentence an innocent to death.

1285
02:11:18,790 --> 02:11:20,870
I implore you, My Lord.

1286
02:11:25,470 --> 02:11:26,990
Kindly retract your verdict.

1287
02:11:30,750 --> 02:11:32,750
This is my final decision, Prince.

1288
02:11:33,390 --> 02:11:35,710
The Jews ought to be
punished for their crimes.

1289
02:11:38,950 --> 02:11:41,870
Is justice blinded by your faith?

1290
02:11:42,190 --> 02:11:44,870
Is your justice based
on hatred and prejudice?

1291
02:11:44,950 --> 02:11:49,150
Marcus. Your words reek of rebellion.

1292
02:11:49,910 --> 02:11:52,710
Perhaps you forget
whom you are talking to.

1293
02:11:53,190 --> 02:11:55,790
In your zeal, you have
become devoid of your senses.

1294
02:11:56,110 --> 02:11:59,670
To speak against injustice,
is the duty of every human being.

1295
02:12:00,470 --> 02:12:02,670
You cannot stifle the
protest of an innocent.

1296
02:12:03,470 --> 02:12:06,830
It will rise like gusty storm
from every corner of the world.

1297
02:12:07,470 --> 02:12:11,712
And they will vanquish your
empires of injustice and slavery.

1298
02:12:11,792 --> 02:12:16,910
Silence, Marcus. Your wayward
tongue challenges my authority.

1299
02:12:20,430 --> 02:12:23,470
..which burns in my heart too,
like those of many others.

1300
02:12:23,830 --> 02:12:25,710
Beware of the revolution, Brutus.

1301
02:12:25,910 --> 02:12:29,590
Or it will consume
you in its own flames.

1302
02:12:30,270 --> 02:12:33,150
Soldiers. Arrest the rebel.

1303
02:12:34,830 --> 02:12:38,150
You will be given a very
light punishment for rebelling.

1304
02:12:39,150 --> 02:12:42,790
You will personally see
your beloved tomorrow..

1305
02:12:42,870 --> 02:12:45,470
..being cast in
a container of boiling oil.

1306
02:12:45,990 --> 02:12:48,469
So that your
audaciousness is put to an end.

1307
02:12:48,590 --> 02:12:50,950
And that a revolution
ensues in your world too.

1308
02:12:53,550 --> 02:12:57,550
Forgive him? So that he gets to
challenge the justice of Rome?

1309
02:12:57,790 --> 02:13:02,470
Octavia, this isn't an insult of
Governor Brutus but of the Roman Empire.

1310
02:13:03,390 --> 02:13:06,510
Whatever Marcus has done is
because of his naivet, My Lord.

1311
02:13:09,950 --> 02:13:15,150
And he will have to pay for it,
so that he never repeats it.

1312
02:13:15,230 --> 02:13:19,469
Yet, My Lord, Marcus
is Rome's Crown Prince.

1313
02:13:20,190 --> 02:13:22,830
Can the law not grant him pardon?

1314
02:13:22,950 --> 02:13:26,990
This empire belongs to Rome,
and the Roman law shall prevail.

1315
02:13:27,230 --> 02:13:30,830
Governor Brutus is the
judge of Roman justice.

1316
02:13:33,790 --> 02:13:36,710
My Lord..
- I am helpless, Octavia.

1317
02:14:16,793 --> 02:14:20,576
Leo! Leo!

1318
02:14:52,510 --> 02:14:54,390
Be patient, my Prince.

1319
02:14:55,310 --> 02:14:59,990
My love and my life are
dying because of Rome.

1320
02:15:07,950 --> 02:15:13,190
But as of now, you must bow
before Rome's law and justice.

1321
02:15:13,270 --> 02:15:16,190
You term atrocity
and cruelty as justice?

1322
02:15:22,750 --> 02:15:26,350
I deem it my duty to rebel
against such law and justice.

1323
02:15:27,350 --> 02:15:30,670
I shall have all of Rome
oppose Brutus' cruelty.

1324
02:15:31,110 --> 02:15:34,950
I shall unmask his faade.

1325
02:15:35,790 --> 02:15:38,550
So that the world can see
his dangerous and true self.

1326
02:15:38,630 --> 02:15:41,590
Yes, Marcus. You can surely do that.

1327
02:15:41,710 --> 02:15:45,630
But do not forget that you are
surrounded by Roman soldiers.

1328
02:15:46,350 --> 02:15:48,870
You are a prisoner, Prince.

1329
02:15:50,390 --> 02:15:55,110
Yes, you are right, Antonio.

1330
02:15:55,440 --> 02:15:59,190
I am surrounded by the
protectors of Roman justice.

1331
02:16:00,270 --> 02:16:01,950
I am rendered helpless.

1332
02:16:02,990 --> 02:16:09,630
So that my innocent Hannah gets
destroyed, and I remain helpless.

1333
02:16:10,510 --> 02:16:14,830
That her screams die near the
executioners and I stay helpless.

1334
02:16:16,110 --> 02:16:22,190
I never knew, Antonio, falling
in love was so grave a crime.

1335
02:16:22,510 --> 02:16:24,630
And that its punishment was so harsh.

1336
02:16:27,390 --> 02:16:34,700
Antonio, there is still time
for dawn. I need your help.

1337
02:16:34,510 --> 02:16:37,110
Antonio can sacrifice
his life for you, Marcus.

1338
02:16:37,469 --> 02:16:42,590
But to think of a Roman
Prince pining for a mere Jewess..

1339
02:16:42,670 --> 02:16:44,950
Hold your tongue, Antonio.

1340
02:16:45,950 --> 02:16:49,230
I will not tolerate
you insulting my love.

1341
02:16:50,190 --> 02:16:53,230
You are alien to my feelings of love.

1342
02:16:56,270 --> 02:17:00,390
Antonio, you can neither hear nor
fathom the cries of my broken heart.

1343
02:17:00,469 --> 02:17:01,510
Prince.

1344
02:17:01,590 --> 02:17:04,230
Antonio, I am going out of my mind.

1345
02:17:09,570 --> 02:17:12,549
What can I do for you? Command me.

1346
02:17:12,629 --> 02:17:15,709
I am not capable of
giving commands, Antonio.

1347
02:17:17,709 --> 02:17:20,509
But I have a request to
make to you, my friend.

1348
02:17:21,230 --> 02:17:22,750
Fetch me some poison.

1349
02:17:23,628 --> 02:17:24,670
Poison?

1350
02:17:25,188 --> 02:17:27,300
Yes, Antonio, it is my last wish.

1351
02:17:27,110 --> 02:17:29,750
I am your friend, not your enemy.

1352
02:17:30,673 --> 02:17:34,270
Ask me my life. But ask not
for something that I cannot give.

1353
02:17:34,670 --> 02:17:37,830
Unfaithful friend. Go away.
I do not even need you anymore.

1354
02:17:38,590 --> 02:17:41,389
I shall douse this raging
fire without seeking your help.

1355
02:17:41,629 --> 02:17:44,869
Remember, Antonio. One bent on
taking his life can do so in many ways.

1356
02:17:45,230 --> 02:17:49,700
Marcus. Marcus. Marcus. Open the door.

1357
02:17:49,309 --> 02:17:54,869
Marcus. Open the door.
Marcus. Open the door, Prince.

1358
02:17:55,790 --> 02:17:57,710
I say, open the door, Marcus.

1359
02:17:57,830 --> 02:17:59,670
Marcus. Open the door.

1360
02:18:01,549 --> 02:18:05,750
Marcus, in the name of
our friendship, open up.

1361
02:18:06,309 --> 02:18:08,389
Prince, open the door.

1362
02:18:09,190 --> 02:18:12,710
I say, open the door,
Marcus. Open the door, Marcus.

1363
02:18:12,790 --> 02:18:16,390
Open up. Or else
I will break open the door.

1364
02:18:18,190 --> 02:18:20,990
Marcus. Marcus. Open the door.

1365
02:18:27,350 --> 02:18:31,350
Marcus, my friend. In the name
of our friendship, open the door.

1366
02:18:31,430 --> 02:18:36,550
In the name of your love, open up.
For Hannah's sake, Marcus, open up.

1367
02:18:37,469 --> 02:18:41,629
Open the door, Marcus,
or I will break open this door.

1368
02:18:41,709 --> 02:18:43,269
Marcus, open..

1369
02:18:54,950 --> 02:18:57,190
Marcus, your eyes..

1370
02:18:57,910 --> 02:19:03,190
I have hidden Hannah forever..

1371
02:19:03,270 --> 02:19:05,990
..in the safe custody
of my eyes, Antonio.

1372
02:19:07,510 --> 02:19:10,230
Now, nobody can
snatch her away from me.

1373
02:19:10,309 --> 02:19:11,629
Marcus.

1374
02:19:11,750 --> 02:19:14,990
Antonio.

1375
02:19:15,870 --> 02:19:20,700
These stone-hearted
people born as humans..

1376
02:19:20,150 --> 02:19:24,750
Now, nobody can coerce me
to witness their atrocities.

1377
02:19:26,110 --> 02:19:29,910
These blind people will
call me blind, won't they?

1378
02:19:30,790 --> 02:19:31,950
Let them.

1379
02:19:34,629 --> 02:19:39,109
Antonio. Antonio,
do not leave me alone.

1380
02:19:42,510 --> 02:19:43,830
Marcus.

1381
02:19:44,389 --> 02:19:48,789
Just once, take me to Hannah, Antonio.

1382
02:19:49,395 --> 02:19:51,990
Just once, I wish to hear her voice.

1383
02:19:52,910 --> 02:19:57,750
It would be enough for me to carry
on with this miserable life, Antonio.

1384
02:20:21,217 --> 02:20:27,900
Jews. The oils in those
containers eagerly await you.

1385
02:20:27,609 --> 02:20:31,769
Beckon your God now to save
you from burning in the oils.

1386
02:20:32,265 --> 02:20:35,490
Brutus, I do not fear death.

1387
02:20:35,757 --> 02:20:38,569
In any case, my days
are already numbered.

1388
02:20:39,115 --> 02:20:42,903
But look at this innocent
girl who has not even seen life.

1389
02:20:43,663 --> 02:20:45,983
I can spare both of
you on one condition.

1390
02:20:46,313 --> 02:20:48,263
Embrace the Roman creed.

1391
02:20:48,821 --> 02:20:51,190
I shall not sell
the garden fearing withering.

1392
02:20:51,644 --> 02:20:54,346
My life I will sacrifice but
intact will remain my integrity.

1393
02:20:55,163 --> 02:21:00,283
Brutus, our bones can melt
away in those burning oils.

1394
02:21:00,723 --> 02:21:03,803
But nothing can
waver our firm integrity.

1395
02:21:03,923 --> 02:21:08,403
Soldiers. Stop staring.
Throw them in the furnaces.

1396
02:21:09,803 --> 02:21:14,203
My Lord, the fault is mine. Kill me
if you must but spare my father.

1397
02:21:14,283 --> 02:21:17,523
I cannot bear to see
my father die with me.

1398
02:21:18,323 --> 02:21:20,723
Hannah. Come on.

1399
02:21:29,563 --> 02:21:30,803
Wait.

1400
02:21:31,963 --> 02:21:34,363
I wish to be kind to the girl.

1401
02:21:36,163 --> 02:21:39,243
Burn the girl first. So that
she cannot see him burn to death.

1402
02:21:39,323 --> 02:21:44,243
No, Brutus. I cannot bear to
see my daughter dying in agony.

1403
02:21:44,483 --> 02:21:49,123
Spare me this horrible sight and
kill me. But have mercy on her.

1404
02:21:49,203 --> 02:21:50,523
Take him away.

1405
02:21:50,883 --> 02:21:54,283
No. Brutus. Mercy.
For God's sake, have mercy.

1406
02:21:54,803 --> 02:21:56,830
Mercy?

1407
02:22:00,363 --> 02:22:03,483
Which man will not
melt hearing this word?

1408
02:22:04,205 --> 02:22:07,843
Cruel Roman.
Fear at least the justice of God.

1409
02:22:08,724 --> 02:22:11,123
Do you not remember
the anguish of losing a child?

1410
02:22:11,923 --> 02:22:14,403
Have you forgotten that
even you once had a daughter..

1411
02:22:14,483 --> 02:22:17,363
..whom somebody had abducted?

1412
02:22:17,843 --> 02:22:20,563
How do you know?
- How do I know?

1413
02:22:22,603 --> 02:22:27,363
I also know that Lydia is
not dead. She is still alive.

1414
02:22:27,443 --> 02:22:29,563
Lydia. My daughter is alive.

1415
02:22:30,443 --> 02:22:34,283
No way. You seek revenge. You lie.

1416
02:22:34,363 --> 02:22:36,363
Well, assume it is a lie.
Come on, Hannah.

1417
02:22:36,483 --> 02:22:39,643
Wait, Ezra. Do you
know where my daughter is?

1418
02:22:39,924 --> 02:22:42,903
Certainly. But I will not say.

1419
02:22:42,983 --> 02:22:47,403
You won't?
I will punish you so badly..

1420
02:22:47,523 --> 02:22:50,683
..that the skies and
the earth will shudder.

1421
02:22:50,763 --> 02:22:53,883
Go ahead. Why delay?

1422
02:22:55,803 --> 02:22:58,403
No. No, Ezra.
For God's sake, tell me, Ezra.

1423
02:22:58,483 --> 02:22:59,923
I won't.

1424
02:23:00,302 --> 02:23:03,200
You won't?
- No. I won't.

1425
02:23:04,323 --> 02:23:09,243
Ezra, this head has never bowed
even before the Emperor of Rome.

1426
02:23:09,403 --> 02:23:12,300
But I bow before you today.

1427
02:23:12,972 --> 02:23:16,563
Have mercy, Ezra. Have mercy.

1428
02:23:16,643 --> 02:23:17,923
Mercy?

1429
02:23:20,323 --> 02:23:23,883
For the first time,
that word has escaped your lips.

1430
02:23:24,403 --> 02:23:28,523
Perhaps you know now that it
is not only the enslaved Jews..

1431
02:23:28,603 --> 02:23:33,283
..who need mercy.
Even the tyrannical Romans need it.

1432
02:23:33,923 --> 02:23:37,683
But how can a poor Jew show you mercy?

1433
02:23:41,923 --> 02:23:44,443
Seek your tyrannical race.

1434
02:23:44,723 --> 02:23:48,830
You have never
taught us anything good.

1435
02:23:48,283 --> 02:23:51,842
Why should I show mercy to
the one who has never been merciful?

1436
02:23:51,963 --> 02:23:56,163
Ezra. Ezra, have pity on me.

1437
02:23:56,683 --> 02:24:00,203
Tell me. For God's sake,
tell me where my Lydia is?

1438
02:24:00,323 --> 02:24:03,300
I pity your helplessness.

1439
02:24:06,555 --> 02:24:08,203
I accept. Anything.

1440
02:24:08,283 --> 02:24:12,683
First hear my condition.
After I reveal everything..

1441
02:24:12,803 --> 02:24:15,963
..you will instantly cast
Hannah into the furnace.

1442
02:24:19,123 --> 02:24:22,523
And wait for Ezra's signal.
Go. Take her away. Tell me now.

1443
02:24:22,603 --> 02:24:24,430
Very well. Then, listen.

1444
02:24:24,643 --> 02:24:31,300
Fifteen years ago, you had thrown
my innocent son Elijah to the lions.

1445
02:24:31,923 --> 02:24:37,243
My servant, Emmanuel, swore revenge.

1446
02:24:38,163 --> 02:24:40,972
In order to douse those flames of
vengeance..

1447
02:24:41,681 --> 02:24:44,283
..he kidnapped your daughter, Lydia.

1448
02:24:45,403 --> 02:24:49,283
But my conscience and
my religion did not permit me..

1449
02:24:49,569 --> 02:24:51,162
..to punish an innocent daughter ..

1450
02:24:51,243 --> 02:24:53,443
..for the crimes of her father.

1451
02:24:53,999 --> 02:24:58,403
I was overwhelmed by mercy,
and chose to forget the past.

1452
02:24:58,483 --> 02:25:01,763
I raised your daughter as my own.

1453
02:25:03,708 --> 02:25:09,363
Yes. A Jew did. A Jew, who,
in your eyes, is born a criminal.

1454
02:25:09,987 --> 02:25:11,562
But where is she?

1455
02:25:11,643 --> 02:25:13,895
Where is she? Look there.

1456
02:25:19,500 --> 02:25:23,370
Lydia. My child.
- Beware. Where are you going?

1457
02:25:23,117 --> 02:25:27,203
Soldiers, kill her.
- Stop. No. This cannot be.

1458
02:25:27,283 --> 02:25:28,723
Why can it not be?

1459
02:25:28,803 --> 02:25:31,963
Just because she is your
daughter now, and not mine?

1460
02:25:36,711 --> 02:25:41,883
Now that you know she is yours,
you are eager to embrace her?

1461
02:25:45,643 --> 02:25:49,643
Executioners, kill her.
- Wait, Ezra. Ezra.

1462
02:25:55,803 --> 02:25:57,830
Hannah.

1463
02:25:59,883 --> 02:26:02,483
Father.

1464
02:26:02,963 --> 02:26:06,363
Do not leave me, father.

1465
02:26:06,542 --> 02:26:10,603
I have no one else but you.

1466
02:26:10,683 --> 02:26:13,403
Don't cry. Do not weep, my child.

1467
02:26:15,163 --> 02:26:19,403
My dear, I cannot bear to see you cry.

1468
02:26:19,963 --> 02:26:25,830
Come, my dear, embrace
your father just once.

1469
02:26:26,283 --> 02:26:28,483
Your voice spews poison.

1470
02:26:28,923 --> 02:26:33,430
Your breath reeks of dead bodies.

1471
02:26:33,315 --> 02:26:37,830
My child, I am undoubtedly a criminal.

1472
02:26:41,637 --> 02:26:47,763
Just once.. just once call me your
father with these innocent lips, Lydia.

1473
02:26:48,720 --> 02:26:51,203
Lydia is dead. I am Hannah.

1474
02:26:51,763 --> 02:26:55,443
My child. Lydia, return. Please.

1475
02:26:55,736 --> 02:26:58,482
Your crimes will return to haunt you,
and you will be punished.

1476
02:26:58,562 --> 02:27:01,243
But I am leaving this
world of hatred forever.

1477
02:27:01,323 --> 02:27:04,483
My child. Lydia. Lydia.

1478
02:27:12,937 --> 02:27:17,203
"Call it a streak of insanity."

1479
02:27:17,772 --> 02:27:21,803
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

1480
02:27:22,283 --> 02:27:26,762
"Call it a streak of insanity."

1481
02:27:26,923 --> 02:27:31,363
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

1482
02:27:31,843 --> 02:27:36,243
"If this you fail to fathom.."

1483
02:27:36,520 --> 02:27:40,763
"..then only you are to be blamed."

1484
02:28:01,643 --> 02:28:03,763
I have nothing left now.

1485
02:28:04,974 --> 02:28:10,385
Have mercy on a lifeless soul,
Prince, and leave me alone.

1486
02:28:10,826 --> 02:28:15,134
So that I can find a grave
for myself in some corner.

1487
02:28:15,215 --> 02:28:16,363
No, Hannah. No.

1488
02:28:16,563 --> 02:28:20,404
Look, I am begging of you
with folded hands. I have lost.

1489
02:28:24,966 --> 02:28:28,203
I accept that my
desires have perished.

1490
02:28:28,480 --> 02:28:31,820
My dreams have been burnt to ashes.

1491
02:28:31,396 --> 02:28:35,130
But don't impose yourself upon
a helpless woman.

1492
02:28:35,210 --> 02:28:37,443
Go away, Prince. Go away.

1493
02:28:40,998 --> 02:28:44,523
Certain constraints killed my love.

1494
02:28:46,321 --> 02:28:50,323
With my own merciless hands, I have
taken out the light of my heart.

1495
02:28:51,391 --> 02:28:54,643
Hannah, there's
present a frightful darkness.

1496
02:28:55,664 --> 02:28:58,523
And this life seems like one long,
never ending journey.

1497
02:28:59,394 --> 02:29:01,805
This path is so..
- Moshe.

1498
02:29:09,380 --> 02:29:10,402
Moshe.

1499
02:29:12,180 --> 02:29:16,830
Your eyes? What have you done?

1500
02:29:17,225 --> 02:29:19,163
I have been punished for my crime.

1501
02:29:20,762 --> 02:29:23,643
I have paid for the
innocent tears that you had shed.

1502
02:29:24,804 --> 02:29:26,443
I have found immense peace now.

1503
02:29:26,923 --> 02:29:31,533
Moshe. Moshe, I seek your forgiveness.

1504
02:29:31,613 --> 02:29:37,162
Overwhelm me with your love once
again. Take me in your arms, Moshe.

1505
02:29:42,975 --> 02:29:44,375
Hannah.

1506
02:29:44,815 --> 02:29:50,895
In the far distance,
I can see the first ray of a new dawn.

1507
02:29:54,992 --> 02:30:00,295
Come, Moshe, let us
touch this new light.

1508
02:30:01,295 --> 02:30:04,775
Let this new dawn be
witness to our love.

1509
02:30:05,953 --> 02:30:07,150
Come.

1510
02:30:10,575 --> 02:30:15,455
"Call it a streak of insanity."

1511
02:30:15,535 --> 02:30:19,975
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

1512
02:30:20,255 --> 02:30:24,775
"Call it a streak of insanity."

1513
02:30:24,855 --> 02:30:29,135
"Or the intoxicating effect of love."

1514
02:30:29,592 --> 02:30:34,175
"If this you fail to fathom.."

1515
02:30:34,255 --> 02:30:38,855
"..then only you are to be blamed."

1516
02:30:38,935 --> 02:30:41,992
"Call it a streak of insanity."

